Had a pretty good meal here.
There's no online menu, so forgive me if I have a few ingredients wrong...
Started with a kale and spinach salad with lemon vinaigrette and parmigiano, which was decent.
At 6$ it's a healthy way to start your meal, although it's a bit one-note and the lemon really starts to get to you about halfway through.
Moved on to a steak sammich served with tots, which again, was decent.
Steak was actually (un)cooked to rare as requested.
Kudos to them for that, but the meat was kinda stringy/chewy.
I had to take a few slices out and cut them myself so they could be edible.
Tots were real good.
Probably wouldn't order again though.
The real problem is that it's just kinda there.
The atmosphere is just OK, you're eating in a plastic chair, there's no TV...
It provides a quick meal for people at The Grand, but if you're in the area are you really skipping all of the better restaurants in the area to come here?
Nope.
Next time I'll test out the deli at the sports book.

