This place is good.
And not just "good for downtown", it's GOOD.
I rarely venture downtown & I always seem to go to the same places; but for tonight's ladies' night, we decided to try something new .. Stewart + Ogden.
When we go out for dinner, we just get a bunch of apps & an entree or two & share .. so, we went for the pub cheese, tuna tataki/poke and the shishito peppers.
I don't know where to begin on these or how to choose my favorite.
I just know that if I'm ever on death row, I want that poke to be a part of my last meal .. Light, fresh & that marinade *drool*.
Anyway, I've never had those kind of peppers before & I'm lucky I got to try them since my mom hogged them all .. charred, tart, not spicy.
Finally, the cheese ..
I want to work here so I can get the recipe & make it for football game gatherings.
Entrees .. steak frites, fried chicken & salmon.
My friend who is a very picky meat eater said it was one of the best steaks she's had in quite some time .. seasoned & cooked perfectly, tender.
The fried chicken was fantastic as well .. juicy with a nice sweetness to it.
The salmon .. oh, that salmon.
It's served with a sweet red pepper sauce (no, it's not siracha) on a cold quinoa salad with mango, corn, black bean, cucumber & red onion .. light, fresh, flavorful and GLUTEN FREE!
As if we hadn't had enough, we also got a few desserts .. the cheesecake is dense, yet light (how?
), the warm brownie is rich (gimme a Newcastle to drink with it) & delicious, and the cinnamon roll bread (or was it sticky bun?
I don't remember, I was starting to enter a food coma) pudding with bourbon sauce .. enter Homer Simpson's drool noise.
All-in-all, we all thoroughly enjoyed our meal .. (I took some pictures; unfortunately, the tuna was destroyed before I remembered to take out the camera) .. and the prices are VERY reasonable.
Will definitely be back.
This restaurant & hotel are going to be a good part of downtown's resurgence .. can't wait!

